# IT Help Desk Ticketing System

A full-stack web application built with the MERN stack that replicates 
core functionality found in enterprise help desk tools like ServiceNow 
and Jira Service Management.

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** React (Vite), Axios
- **Backend:** Node.js, Express.js
- **Database:** MongoDB, Mongoose
- **Tools:** Postman, MongoDB Compass, nodemon

## Features

- Create tickets with title, description, requester, category, and priority
- Auto-generated ticket IDs (TKT-0001 format)
- Status workflow: Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed
- Priority levels: Low, Medium, High, Critical
- Add timestamped technician notes to any ticket
- Live dashboard showing Open, In Progress, Critical, and Resolved counts
- Search by ticket ID, title, or requester
- Filter by status and priority

## Setup Instructions

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (LTS)
- MongoDB Community Server running locally on port 27017

### Backend
```bash
cd backend
npm install
npx nodemon server.js
```

### Frontend
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open http://localhost:5173 in your browser.

## API Endpoints

| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | /api/tickets | Return all tickets |
| GET | /api/tickets/:id | Return single ticket |
| POST | /api/tickets | Create a new ticket |
| PUT | /api/tickets/:id | Update status, priority, or add note |
| DELETE | /api/tickets/:id | Delete a ticket |

## Certification Alignment

- **CompTIA Security+** — REST API authentication concepts, input validation
- **CompTIA Network+** — HTTP methods, client-server communication
- **Splunk Core** — Structured data fields, ticket lifecycle as log events

